{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0112D3aucMb8hPttFcqp878N","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The secret hasn't propagated yet to the ES pod. Let me wait for it.\n\nActually, looking at the files mounted:\n- `users` file is at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/users` (subPath mount)\n- `users_roles` is at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/users_roles` (subPath mount)\n\n**Important**: When a secret is mounted with `subPath`, Kubernetes does NOT automatically update the file when the secret changes. This is a known limitation of Kubernetes - `subPath` mounts are not auto-updated.\nSo I can't just update the secret and wait for propagation. I need to force a rolling restart to get the pods to pick up the new secret. I could mount the secret without subPath instead, but that would change the volume configuration. The bigger issue is that I need to add sidecars to the pods anyway, which means I'll need to restart them regardless.\n\nMy plan is to create ConfigMaps for the Metricbeat and Filebeat configs, then patch the StatefulSet to add the sidecar containers and volumes. The rolling restart triggered by the StatefulSet patch will handle both the secret propagation and the new sidecar configuration.\n\nNow I need to figure out the passwords for `ops-user` and `report-user` from the file realm hashes.\n\nActually, I realize I don't have those passwords, but I can add `monitoring-internal` with a known password. When the StatefulSet restarts due to the patch, the pods will pick up the latest secret version, so the new user will be available to the sidecars.\n\nLet me work out the complete StatefulSet patch, starting with the volumes I need to add: `es-logs` as an emptyDir, plus ConfigMaps for both Metricbeat and Filebeat configurations.\n\nFor Metricbeat, I'm configuring it to scrape the local Elasticsearch node over HTTPS using the CA certificate, then ship metrics to the monitoring cluster via